---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
	title="ThingsBoard IoT Hub Privacy Policy"
	description="ThingsBoard IoT Hub Privacy Policy"
>
	<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
	<p class="date">Last Updated: June 14, 2026</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>1. Introduction</b></p>
	<p>
		This Privacy Policy describes how ThingsBoard, Inc. ("ThingsBoard," "we," "us," or "our")
		collects, uses, stores, and discloses information in connection with the ThingsBoard IoT Hub
		(the "IoT Hub"). By accessing or using the IoT Hub, you agree to the practices described in
		this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please discontinue use of the IoT Hub.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>2. Information We Collect</b></p>
	<p>When you register or interact with the IoT Hub, we may collect the following types of data:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Account Information:</b> Your name, display name or username, email address, and login
			credentials created during registration.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Organization Information:</b> Your company or organization name, if you are submitting
			Contributions on behalf of an entity.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Contribution Metadata:</b> Title, description, tags, categorization, authorship
			attribution, submission timestamps, and version history associated with any Contribution
			you publish.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Usage Data:</b> IP address, approximate geographic location, browser type, operating
			system, device identifiers, pages viewed, download activity, and search queries collected
			automatically when you access the IoT Hub.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Communications:</b> The content of any messages you send us for support or other
			inquiries, along with your contact details.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>3. How We Use Your Information</b></p>
	<p>We use the information collected for the following purposes:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Platform Operation:</b> To provide, maintain, and improve the IoT Hub, including
			processing Contributions and enabling downloads.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Attribution:</b> To credit you as the Author of your Contributions, consistent with the
			MIT License and the IoT Hub Terms of Use.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Access Control & Security:</b> To authenticate users, detect malicious code or policy
			violations, and enforce the Terms of Use.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Communication:</b> To notify you about updates to your Contributions, policy changes,
			or responses to your inquiries.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Analytics:</b> To understand usage patterns and improve platform features and
			searchability.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Legal Compliance:</b> To comply with applicable laws, respond to lawful requests, and
			enforce our agreements.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>4. Data Sharing</b></p>
	<p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information only in the following circumstances:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Public Contributions:</b> Contributions you publish on the IoT Hub, including their
			metadata and authorship attribution, are publicly accessible by all users of the IoT Hub
			and the ThingsBoard platform. Do not include personal or sensitive information within the
			content of your Contributions.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Service Providers:</b> We may share information with trusted third-party providers who
			assist us in operating the IoT Hub (e.g., hosting, analytics, security). These providers
			are contractually obligated to process data only on our behalf and in accordance with this
			Privacy Policy.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Legal Compliance:</b> If required by law, regulation, or legal process, or to protect
			the rights, property, or safety of ThingsBoard, Inc., its users, or the public.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Business Transfers:</b> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your
			information may be transferred as part of that transaction. We will notify you via the
			email address associated with your account prior to any such transfer.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>5. Irrevocability of Published Contributions</b></p>
	<p>
		Consistent with the IoT Hub Terms of Use, the license granted over a published Contribution
		is irrevocable. Metadata and authorship attribution associated with a Contribution that has
		already been downloaded or implemented by other users will remain accessible even after you
		remove the Contribution from the IoT Hub. ThingsBoard, Inc. cannot retroactively withdraw
		publicly available information that has already been accessed or cached by users or
		third-party systems.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>6. Data Retention & Deletion</b></p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Retention:</b> We retain your personal information for as long as your account remains
			active or as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy.
			Contribution metadata and authorship records are retained indefinitely to preserve the
			integrity of the MIT License attribution chain.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Account Deletion:</b> You may request deletion of your account at any time. Upon
			deletion, we will remove or anonymize your personal account data within a reasonable time,
			subject to legal retention obligations and the irrevocability provisions described above.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>7. Security</b></p>
	<p>
		ThingsBoard, Inc. implements reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your
		information against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission
		over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute
		security.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>8. Children's Privacy</b></p>
	<p>
		The IoT Hub is not directed to individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect
		personal information from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such
		information, please contact us and we will promptly delete it.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>9. Your Rights</b></p>
	<p>
		Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to access, correct, delete, or
		restrict processing of your personal information, or to request a portable copy of your data.
		To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details in Section 10.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>10. Contact Us</b></p>
	<p>
		If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at <a
			href="mailto:sales@thingsboard.io">sales@thingsboard.io</a>.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</b></p>
	<p>
		ThingsBoard, Inc. reserves the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Material
		changes will be communicated by updating the date at the top of this document and, where
		appropriate, by direct notification to registered users. Your continued use of the IoT Hub
		after any such changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.
	</p>
</LegalLayout>
